{
  "esm": "0.5.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "GEOSFP",
    "description": "GEOS-FP (Goddard Earth Observing System Forward Processing) atmospheric data loader as archived for use with GEOS-Chem classic. Provides 6 file-type collections covering 2D surface and 3D pressure-level meteorological fields at 0.25° × 0.3125° global resolution (the default domain; regional and coarser domains are also available — see domain_note in data_loaders metadata). Data are sourced from the AWS S3 mirror (geos-chem.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com) and are archived from approximately 2013-01-01 to near-real-time.\n\nSix file-type collections are provided:\n  A1  — 1-hourly time-averaged 2D surface fields (24 records/day; center times 00:30, 01:30, ..., 23:30 UTC)\n  A3cld — 3-hourly averaged 3D cloud properties (8 records/day; center times 01:30, ..., 22:30 UTC)\n  A3dyn — 3-hourly averaged 3D dynamical fields (8 records/day; U, V, OMEGA, RH, DTRAIN)\n  A3mstC — 3-hourly averaged 3D moist convective fields (8 records/day)\n  A3mstE — 3-hourly averaged 3D moist extra fields (8 records/day)\n  I3  — 3-hourly instantaneous 3D fields (8 records/day; times 00:00, 03:00, ..., 21:00 UTC)\n\nThe GEOS-FP vertical coordinate is a terrain-following hybrid sigma-pressure system with 72 model layers (73 interfaces). Pressure at level lev is P = Ap[lev] + Bp[lev] × PS, where Ap and Bp are the hybrid coordinate coefficients tabulated for lev=1 (bottom interface, P≈PS≈101325 Pa) to lev=73 (top of atmosphere, P≈1 Pa). The coefficients are embedded in GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs.\n\nThe gt-p3ep (@register_symbolic interp_unsafe) blocking gap is resolved by the data_loaders §8 mechanism for all six file-type collections. The gt-6ohw (DataInterpolations.derivative) blocking gap affects only δPδlev and δZδlev (which require the derivative of the Ap/Bp interpolation with respect to lev); those variables are omitted and documented in reference.notes.\n\nStaggering: A3dyn.U is x-edge-staggered (lon edges), A3dyn.V is y-edge-staggered (lat edges), A3dyn.OMEGA is z-edge-staggered (lev interfaces). All other variables are cell-centered.\n\nMigrated from EarthSciData.jl@830435a065f27e99f10bba91107ca1730322cc6b:src/geosfp.jl:410 (GEOSFP constructor, esm-1c6s).",
    "tags": [
      "earthsci_data",
      "meteorology",
      "atmospheric_dynamics",
      "data_loader",
      "geos_fp",
      "global",
      "hybrid_pressure",
      "geos_chem",
      "nasa"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-30T00:00:00Z",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciData.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-1c6s)"
    ],
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "GEOS-FP data archived for GEOS-Chem classic. NASA Global Modeling and Assimilation Office (GMAO). AWS S3 mirror: s3://geos-chem/GEOS_{domain}/GEOS_FP/. See http://geoschemdata.wustl.edu/ExtData/ for current domain and file-type options.",
        "url": "http://geoschemdata.wustl.edu/ExtData/"
      },
      {
        "citation": "Molod, A., Takacs, L., Suarez, M., and Bacmeister, J. (2015). Development of the GEOS-5 atmospheric general circulation model: evolution from MERRA to MERRA2. Geosci. Model Dev., 8, 1339–1356.",
        "doi": "10.5194/gmd-8-1339-2015"
      },
      {
        "citation": "GEOS-Chem vertical grid documentation: https://wiki.seas.harvard.edu/geos-chem/index.php/GEOS-Chem_vertical_grids",
        "url": "https://wiki.seas.harvard.edu/geos-chem/index.php/GEOS-Chem_vertical_grids"
      },
      {
        "citation": "Source: EarthSciData.jl@830435a065f27e99f10bba91107ca1730322cc6b:src/geosfp.jl (GEOSFPFileSet, GEOSFP constructor, Ap/Bp hybrid grid coefficients, geosfp_staggering). Test: test/geosfp_test.jl. Docs: docs present in pinned commit."
      }
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "GEOSFP": {
      "coupletype": "GEOSFPCoupler",
      "reference": {
        "notes": "source_ref: EarthSciData.jl@830435a065f27e99f10bba91107ca1730322cc6b:src/geosfp.jl:410\n\nUpstream GEOSFP(domain, domaininfo; name=:GEOSFP, stream=true, spatial_interp=:linear) creates an MTK System with:\n  - @parameters: lon/lat (rad) and lev (1) from pvars(domaininfo); t_ref (s)\n  - For every varname in every GEOSFPFileSet collection (A1/A3cld/A3dyn/A3mstC/A3mstE/I3),\n    one DataSetInterpolator and one observed equation via create_interp_equation (uses interp_unsafe)\n  - Coordinate mapping: lon/lat in radians (loadmetadata converts from degrees); lev=1..72\n  - Staggering: geosfp_staggering() returns:\n      A3dyn/U   → (true, false, false)  # x-staggered (lon edges)\n      A3dyn/V   → (false, true, false)  # y-staggered (lat edges)\n      A3dyn/OMEGA → (false, false, true)  # z-staggered (lev interfaces)\n      all others → (false, false, false) # cell-centered\n  - Extrapolation: OMEGA uses zero extrapolation (extrapolate_type=0.0); all others use Flat() (clamp)\n  - Hybrid pressure: P ~ P_unit * Ap(lev) + Bp(lev) * I3₊PS\n    where Ap/Bp are DataInterpolations.LinearInterpolation tables indexed 1:73\n    (lev=1 → surface ≈ PS, lev=73 → 1 Pa). Encoded in GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs data_loader.\n  - Virtual temperature: Tv ~ T * (1 + 0.61 * QV); Tv_sfc ~ T2M * (1 + 0.61 * QV2M)\n  - Layer-mean virtual temp: Tv̄ ~ 0.5 * (Tv + Tv_sfc)\n  - Coordinate metrics (lat/lon domain only): δxδlon ~ lon2m * cos(lat); δyδlat ~ lat2meters\n  - discrete_events: build_interp_event fires at each file collection boundary to reload buffers\n  - metadata: Dict(CoupleType => GEOSFPCoupler, SysDomainInfo => domaininfo)\n  - couple2 with MeanWindCoupler: maps GEOSFP.A3dyn₊U/V/OMEGA → MeanWind v_lon/v_lat/v_lev\n\ngt-p3ep resolution: the @register_symbolic interp_unsafe pattern for all file-variable equations is replaced by the data_loaders §8 mechanism (GEOSFP_A1.*, GEOSFP_A3*.*, GEOSFP_I3.* references). The Ap/Bp hybrid coordinate tables are represented via GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs (kind: lookup) with embedded coefficient values, resolving the fixed-table lookup gap for P.\n\ngt-6ohw gap (DataInterpolations.derivative): δPδlev and δZδlev require the symbolic derivative of Ap(lev) and Bp(lev) with respect to lev (via DataInterpolations.derivative), which is not yet representable in the ESM expression language. These variables are omitted. When gt-6ohw is resolved:\n  δPδlev (Pa): d(P)/d(lev) = d(Ap(lev))/d(lev) + d(Bp(lev))/d(lev) * PS\n    For the linear interpolation with unit spacing: d(Ap)/d(lev) at integer lev n = Ap[n+1]-Ap[n]\n    The upstream code uses: expand_derivatives(Differential(lev)(P_unit * Ap(lev) + Bp(lev) * PS))\n  δZδlev (m): d(Z_agl)/d(lev) — requires Pmid = P_unit*Ap(lev+0.5)+Bp(lev+0.5)*PS (gt-p3ep(lookup)\n    with lev+0.5 offset) and derivatives of Ap/Bp at lev+0.5 (gt-6ohw). Both gaps must be resolved.\n\nZ_agl gap (gt-p3ep(lookup)): Z_agl = (Rd * Tv̄ / g) * log(PS / Pmid) where\n  Pmid = P_unit * Ap(lev+0.5) + Bp(lev+0.5) * PS\n  Evaluating Ap and Bp at the fractional level lev+0.5 is an offset-indexed lookup (gt-p3ep(lookup))\n  not yet representable in the ESM expression language. Z_agl is omitted; when gt-p3ep(lookup) is\n  resolved, add:\n    Pmid = GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs.Ap_at_lev_plus_half + GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs.Bp_at_lev_plus_half * I3₊PS\n    Z_agl = (287.05 * Tv̄ / 9.80665) * log(I3₊PS / Pmid)\n\nUpstream test values at (-155.7°, 39.1°) for domain '4x5' (EarthSciData.jl test/geosfp_test.jl):\n  P at lev=[1,2,3,71,72,73]: [102340.38, 101572.77, 100805.17, 2.0, 1.5, 1.0] Pa\n  OMEGA at lev=[0.5,1,1.5,2,35,70,72.5]: [0.0, -0.00385, -0.00770, -0.00652, 1.12e-5, 0.0, 0.0] Pa/s\n  Z_agl at various levels: 63.38 m (lev=1.5) to 80132.64 m (lev=72.5)\n\nDomain notes: the default domain '0.25x0.3125' is the native GEOS-FP global grid. Regional and coarser domains (e.g. '4x5', '0.25x0.3125_NA', '2x2.5') change the URL prefix GEOS_{domain}/GEOS_FP/ and the filename suffix. The transformed domain in the filename replaces dots with nothing and underscores with dots: '0.25x0.3125_NA' → '025x03125.NA'. This ESM documents the default 0.25x0.3125 global domain."
      },
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-06
      },
      "variables": {
        "lon": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "rad",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Longitude of the model grid point (radians). Coupled to the simulation domain's longitude coordinate via param_to_var. Used for GEOSFP data spatial interpolation."
        },
        "lat": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "rad",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Latitude of the model grid point (radians). Coupled to the simulation domain's latitude coordinate via param_to_var. Used for GEOSFP data spatial interpolation."
        },
        "lev": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Hybrid vertical level index (dimensionless, 1-based). lev=1 is the bottom interface (P≈PS, near-surface); lev=73 is the top interface (P≈1 Pa). Layer centers are at lev=1.5, 2.5, ..., 72.5. Interpolation within the Ap/Bp tables is linear with unit spacing."
        },
        "t_ref": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "units": "s",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Reference epoch (seconds since the Julia DateTime epoch) from which the GEOS-FP file time axis is offset. Set from DomainInfo.get_tref(domaininfo) at construction time."
        },
        "T": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "K",
          "description": "Air temperature (K). 3-hourly instantaneous 3D field on the GEOS-FP hybrid pressure levels. Sourced from GEOSFP_I3.T. Used in virtual temperature calculation Tv = T * (1 + 0.61*QV).",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_I3.T"
        },
        "QV": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg",
          "description": "Specific humidity of water vapor (kg/kg). 3-hourly instantaneous 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_I3.QV. Used in virtual temperature calculation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_I3.QV"
        },
        "PS": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "Pa",
          "description": "Surface pressure (Pa). 3-hourly instantaneous 2D field (no lev dimension). Used in hybrid pressure calculation P = Ap[lev] + Bp[lev]*PS. Sourced from GEOSFP_I3.PS.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_I3.PS"
        },
        "T2M": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "K",
          "description": "Air temperature at 2m above the displacement height (K). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D surface field. Used in near-surface virtual temperature Tv_sfc = T2M * (1 + 0.61*QV2M). Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.T2M.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.T2M"
        },
        "QV2M": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg",
          "description": "Specific humidity at 2m (kg/kg). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D surface field. Used in near-surface virtual temperature Tv_sfc. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.QV2M.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.QV2M"
        },
        "U10M": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/s",
          "description": "Eastward wind at 10m above the displacement height (m/s). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D surface field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.U10M.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.U10M"
        },
        "V10M": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/s",
          "description": "Northward wind at 10m above the displacement height (m/s). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D surface field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.V10M.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.V10M"
        },
        "PBLH": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m",
          "description": "Planetary boundary layer height (m). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.PBLH.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.PBLH"
        },
        "PRECTOT": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Total precipitation rate (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field (large-scale plus convective). Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.PRECTOT.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.PRECTOT"
        },
        "PRECANV": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Anvil precipitation rate (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.PRECANV.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.PRECANV"
        },
        "SLP": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "Pa",
          "description": "Sea-level pressure (Pa). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.SLP.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.SLP"
        },
        "TS": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "K",
          "description": "Surface skin temperature (K). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.TS.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.TS"
        },
        "CLDTOT": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Total cloud fraction (dimensionless, 0–1). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.CLDTOT.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.CLDTOT"
        },
        "SWGDN": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "W/m^2",
          "description": "Incident shortwave flux at the ground (W m⁻²). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.SWGDN.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.SWGDN"
        },
        "TROPP_H": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "Pa",
          "description": "Tropopause pressure using the thermal definition (Pa). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.TROPP_H.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.TROPP_H"
        },
        "FRSEAICE": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Sea ice area fraction (dimensionless, 0–1). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.FRSEAICE.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.FRSEAICE"
        },
        "GWETTOP": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Topsoil moisture (volumetric, dimensionless). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.GWETTOP.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.GWETTOP"
        },
        "LAI": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Leaf area index (m² leaf per m² ground, dimensionless). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.LAI.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.LAI"
        },
        "USTAR": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/s",
          "description": "Surface friction velocity (m/s). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.USTAR.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.USTAR"
        },
        "Z0M": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m",
          "description": "Surface roughness length for momentum (m). 1-hourly time-averaged 2D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A1.Z0M.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A1.Z0M"
        },
        "U": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/s",
          "description": "Eastward wind component (m/s). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Cell-center staggered in y and z; x-edge-staggered (lon-edge aligned, de-staggered by runtime). Sourced from GEOSFP_A3dyn.U. Coupled to MeanWind.v_lon via GEOSFPCoupler/couple2. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3dyn.U"
        },
        "V": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/s",
          "description": "Northward wind component (m/s). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. y-edge-staggered (lat-edge aligned, de-staggered by runtime). Sourced from GEOSFP_A3dyn.V. Coupled to MeanWind.v_lat via GEOSFPCoupler/couple2. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3dyn.V"
        },
        "OMEGA": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "Pa/s",
          "description": "Vertical pressure velocity (Pa/s). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. z-edge-staggered (lev-interface aligned, de-staggered by runtime). Sourced from GEOSFP_A3dyn.OMEGA. Coupled to MeanWind.v_lev via GEOSFPCoupler/couple2. Zero extrapolation (extrapolate_type=0.0) to prevent spurious vertical mass transport.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3dyn.OMEGA"
        },
        "RH": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Relative humidity with respect to liquid water (dimensionless, 0–1). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3dyn.RH. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3dyn.RH"
        },
        "DTRAIN": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Detrainment of cloud mass (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3dyn.DTRAIN. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3dyn.DTRAIN"
        },
        "CLOUD": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "3D cloud fraction (dimensionless, 0–1). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3cld.CLOUD. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3cld.CLOUD"
        },
        "QI": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg",
          "description": "Mass fraction of cloud ice water (kg/kg). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3cld.QI. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3cld.QI"
        },
        "QL": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg",
          "description": "Mass fraction of cloud liquid water (kg/kg). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3cld.QL. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3cld.QL"
        },
        "OPTDEPTH": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Grid-mean cloud optical depth at visible wavelengths (dimensionless). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3cld.OPTDEPTH. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3cld.OPTDEPTH"
        },
        "TAUCLI": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Optical thickness of convective ice cloud (dimensionless). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3cld.TAUCLI. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3cld.TAUCLI"
        },
        "TAUCLW": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "1",
          "description": "Optical thickness of convective liquid cloud (dimensionless). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3cld.TAUCLW. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3cld.TAUCLW"
        },
        "CMFMC": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Upward moist convective mass flux (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstC.CMFMC. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstC.CMFMC"
        },
        "DQRCU": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg/s",
          "description": "Convective rain production (kg kg⁻¹ s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstC.DQRCU. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstC.DQRCU"
        },
        "DQRLSAN": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg/s",
          "description": "Large-scale rain and snow production (kg kg⁻¹ s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstC.DQRLSAN. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstC.DQRLSAN"
        },
        "REEEVAP": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/kg/s",
          "description": "Evaporation of convective precipitation (kg kg⁻¹ s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstC.REEEVAP. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstC.REEEVAP"
        },
        "CMFMC_OCE": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Downward moist convective mass flux from ocean (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstE.CMFMC_OCE. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstE.CMFMC_OCE"
        },
        "PFICU": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Downward flux of ice mass from convection (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFICU. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFICU"
        },
        "PFILSAN": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Downward flux of ice mass from large-scale precipitation and snowfall (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFILSAN. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFILSAN"
        },
        "PFLCU": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Downward flux of liquid mass from convection (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFLCU. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFLCU"
        },
        "PFLLSAN": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "kg/m^2/s",
          "description": "Downward flux of liquid mass from large-scale precipitation and snowfall (kg m⁻² s⁻¹). 3-hourly time-averaged 3D field. Sourced from GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFLLSAN. Clamp extrapolation.",
          "expression": "GEOSFP_A3mstE.PFLLSAN"
        },
        "P": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "Pa",
          "description": "Total atmospheric pressure (Pa) on the GEOS-FP hybrid sigma-pressure vertical coordinate. P = Ap[lev] + Bp[lev] × PS, where Ap and Bp are the hybrid A/B interface coefficients for GEOS-Chem 72-level grid (lev=1: surface ≈ 101325 Pa; lev=73: top ≈ 1 Pa) and PS is the surface pressure. Coefficients sourced from GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "+",
            "args": [
              "GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs.Ap",
              {
                "op": "*",
                "args": [
                  "GEOSFP_hybrid_coefs.Bp",
                  "GEOSFP_I3.PS"
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "Tv": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "K",
          "description": "Virtual temperature at pressure level (K). Tv = T × (1 + 0.61 × QV), where T is air temperature and QV is specific humidity. Used in geopotential height calculation Z_agl (which is omitted due to gt-p3ep(lookup); see reference.notes).",
          "expression": {
            "op": "*",
            "args": [
              "GEOSFP_I3.T",
              {
                "op": "+",
                "args": [
                  1.0,
                  {
                    "op": "*",
                    "args": [
                      0.61,
                      "GEOSFP_I3.QV"
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "Tv_sfc": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "K",
          "description": "Near-surface virtual temperature at 2m (K). Tv_sfc = T2M × (1 + 0.61 × QV2M). Used in layer-mean virtual temperature Tv̄.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "*",
            "args": [
              "GEOSFP_A1.T2M",
              {
                "op": "+",
                "args": [
                  1.0,
                  {
                    "op": "*",
                    "args": [
                      0.61,
                      "GEOSFP_A1.QV2M"
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "Tv_bar": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "K",
          "description": "Layer-mean virtual temperature (K). Tv̄ = 0.5 × (Tv + Tv_sfc). Used in Z_agl hypsometric height calculation (omitted; see reference.notes).",
          "expression": {
            "op": "*",
            "args": [
              0.5,
              {
                "op": "+",
                "args": [
                  "Tv",
                  "Tv_sfc"
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "δxδlon": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/rad",
          "description": "Coordinate metric: x-distance per unit longitude (m rad⁻¹). δxδlon = lon2m × cos(lat) where lon2m = 40075×10³/(2π) ≈ 6378134.3 m rad⁻¹. Emitted only in lat/lon coordinate domains.",
          "expression": {
            "op": "*",
            "args": [
              6378134.3,
              {
                "op": "cos",
                "args": [
                  "lat"
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "δyδlat": {
          "type": "observed",
          "units": "m/rad",
          "description": "Coordinate metric: y-distance per unit latitude (m rad⁻¹). δyδlat = lat2meters = 111.32×10³×(180/π) ≈ 6378166.0 m rad⁻¹. Constant. Emitted only in lat/lon coordinate domains.",
          "expression": 6378166.0
        }
      },
      "equations": [],
      "tests": []
    }
  },
